items.name: sword

analysis.name: Low Poly Short Sword
analysis.styleNotes: A low-poly, untextured model of a medieval short sword. It uses a minimal number of flat-shaded polygons, giving it a stylized, geometric appearance. The design consists of basic shapes with solid colors, suitable for fantasy or historical games with a minimalist art style.

items.name: staff2

analysis.name: Runic Crystal Staff
analysis.styleNotes: A low-poly fantasy mage staff designed with simple geometric shapes. The main shaft is a twisted brown prism, giving it an organic, wooden feel. The top features a large, faceted blue crystal, likely an icosahedron (a low-detail sphere), held in place by four sharp, metallic claws. The shaft is adorned with glowing purple runes, which would be an emissive texture map. The base is finished with a pointed metallic tip, matching the claws. The overall aesthetic is stylized and unlit, suitable for fast-rendering games.

items.name: sword2

analysis.name: Low Poly Sword
analysis.styleNotes: A classic low-poly medieval sword. The model is characterized by its faceted surfaces, flat shading, and a simple color palette. The construction uses basic geometric primitives, creating a stylized and clean look suitable for fantasy or medieval-themed games. The lighting model should emphasize the flat planes of the geometry to enhance the low-poly aesthetic.

items.name: sword3

analysis.name: Low Poly Short Sword
analysis.styleNotes: A classic medieval short sword rendered in a low-poly style with flat shading. The model features distinct, visible polygons creating a faceted look. The blade has a prominent central ridge, giving it a diamond cross-section, tapering to a sharp point. The hilt is modeled to simulate a spiral leather wrap, and the weapon is completed with a simple, angular crossguard and a faceted spherical pommel.

items.name: sword4

analysis.name: Low Poly Shortsword
analysis.styleNotes: A low-polygon, faceted 3D model of a classic shortsword. The model features a distinct non-smoothed aesthetic with visible flat faces. The blade is double-edged and tapers to a sharp point, with a central ridge suggested by the geometry. The hilt has a spiral wrap implied by its faceted cylindrical shape. The crossguard and pommel are also constructed with clear, angular facets, giving the entire asset a stylized, game-ready appearance.
